      <div class="container form_details">
      		<div id="vision_form" style="display:block">
      			<article>
	      			<h4>Vision</h4>
	      			<p>
	      				What is the most important thing or the biggest challenge to the students who are about to graduate from universities? Definitely finding a satisfactory job! However, in fact, it is not easy, and students actually spend much time to try to get jobs. What can we do now to help students finding jobs and starting their career? In general, we search jobs on some websites which publish jobs for all people who are looking for jobs. These websites include Seek, SJS, TradeMe, etc. Some students know more about these websites, and other students only know a few. As we known, some websites also can automatically search jobs information based on keywords and send it to the user's mailbox, and some websites not.
	      			</p>
	      			<p>
	      				We would like to develop a tool that can help the students to automatically search job information according to what they have learned and the skills they are good at; and push these job information to the mailboxes of the students; it should be very convenient and useful. At the same time, the job information that some students have got can also be shared with their good friends or other students through the tool; thus the students can get more accurate job information in time. To the corporations, they can also publish job information; and the information can be automatically matched with the students who have suitable skills, and pushed directly to the students. This tool would be a win-win outcome for both sides of the job information.
	      			</p>
	      			<hr>
	      			<p align="right">Group Members: YUTAO WANG, YU XIAO, XIANZE HE and YANG GAO.</p>
      			</article>
